name: The Many Tails of Jiril the Squirrel

pages.content: Jiril the squirrel sat on the branch of a tree. He was all alone.
Jiril felt lonely. He wished he could play with his friends.
He ran down the tree to the ground. He did not find his friends but he did find an acorn to eat.

Jiril looked and looked for his friends but he could not find them.  
He took a nap because he was tired.

When Jiril woke up, he decided to climb the tree again. 
But he was still half asleep and he rolled down to the ground.
Soon he found his friends playing and eating. Jiril was happy now as he was not alone.
